questions.question_text_1: A doctor sees patients in his consulting room every evening. A certain number of appointments are given for each evening. Patients can also take a chance and come without an appointment. Appointments are not for a fixed time. The receptionist allows patients in to see the doctor in the order in which they arrive, with the provision that any patient with an appointment goes in before any patient without an appointment. What would be a good data structure for the receptionist to keep track of the waiting patients?
